    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe ui2 pager breaks when displaying the message caused by running `vim.pack.update()`. I suspect this is not a problem with specifically `vim.pack` and can be triggered in other ways, but this is where I discovered it.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- Add any package with `vim.pack` so that `vim.pack.update()` can see it.\n- Run `nvim --clean`.\n- Run `:lua require('vim._extui').enable { enabled = true }`\n- Run `:lua vim.pack.update()`\n- Type `g<`.\n- Observe the broken highlighting.\n- Type `:` to enter command mode.\n- You will see double 'fillchars' msgsep, and upon exiting command mode, the cursor will be on a msgsep character.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNothing breaks.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev+1640- 4b8980949\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 43\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.43.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nFedora COPR",
